{"author":"Iso Tester","data":{"body":"Wrote docs/repo-snapshot-gates.md (the central doc) + credential requirement in README.md (MCP-setup) and docs/jira-sync-setup.md. AC1 README + jira-sync-setup state the private-repo fetch-credential requirement + how to supply it (grep-able 'credential'/'private'/'fetch' + xref to the full doc); AC2 descriptive missing-credential error (SnapshotFetchError message+remedy) + fail-closed (attested) vs local-still-runs in repo-snapshot-gates.md; AC3 ref/source semantics + origin/main default + signs-vs-never-signs + verified_at_sha for CLI+MCP; AC4 HMAC trust model + limits (no non-repudiation/public-verifiability/transparency) + the in-toto v1 Statement shape; AC5 REBAR_GATE_TMPDIR + disk-cap watermark behavior + EFS/NFS flock caveat (xref alto-fruit-punch). Also recorded the pinned one-to-one CLI<->MCP mapping + cwd/branch decoupling in ADR 0005 (D7). A grep-able doc test (tests/unit/test_snapshot_docs.py) pins every named section. Subagent doc-accuracy review: NO blocking issues — every load-bearing claim verified TRUE against the implementation (env var names, default values, error classes, HMAC/in-toto shape, close-gate=HEAD vs MCP=origin/main). 5 doc tests green."},"env_id":"ade0f2ef-51cc-45a2-bb97-c09846cd3df5","event_type":"COMMENT","timestamp":1782545304369164001,"uuid":"5a22d82e-5e8b-4239-af12-9b66ba61a16d"}